aaron’s jazz music report

Updated: Mar 30, 2024 (15:00 MDT)

About

I started listening to jazz music in 2020 and have been documenting the jazz releases that I’ve listened to since.

This webpage describes the various characteristics of these jazz releases using data from Rate Your Music which has a database of 88,266 jazz releases (albums, EPs, singles).

Quick Stats

Currently, I have listened to 755 jazz releases.

Genres

  • I listen to most frequently: Avant-Garde Jazz, Post-Bop, Hard Bop, Free Jazz, and Spiritual Jazz.

  • I particularly enjoy: Spiritual Jazz, Stride, Modal Jazz, Hard Bop and Post-Bop.

  • I tend to avoid: Smooth Jazz, Swing Revival, Soul Jazz, British Dance Band, and Vocal Jazz.

Years

  • I listen to most frequently: 1965, 1961, 1966, 1957, and 1959.

  • I need to listen to more: 1960, 1976, 1956, 1994, and 2015.

Musicians

  • I listen to most frequently: John Coltrane, Miles Davis, Thelonious Monk, Anthony Braxton, and Sun Ra.

  • My favorite jazz musician is Anthony Braxton and my favorite jazz album is Six Monk’s Compositions (1987).
